     <h2>
      About Me
     </h2>
     <div class="about-content">
      <div class="elementor-widget-container">
       <p>
I'm a Research Scientist at Roblox, where I work on avatars and animation. My broader research focuses on 3D computer vision, point cloud processing, and deep learning for 3D understanding. I believe in making research accessible—publishing open-source code and hosting conversations with researchers. PhD from the Technion (plus B.Sc Cum Laude, M.Sc Summa Cum Laude).
        </p>
        <p>
         <strong>Wondering</strong> <a href="blog/posts/2021-03-10-how-to-pronounce-my-name.html"><strong>how to say my name</strong></a><strong>? I got you covered.</strong>
                </p>
        <p>
         In my spare time, I host the <a href="https://talking.papers.podcast.itzikbs.com/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Talking Papers Podcast</a>, providing a platform for early career academics to discuss their latest research. Here you can explore my <a href="https://www.itzikbs.com/publications/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">publications</a>, <a href="https://www.itzikbs.com/code/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">code</a>, and <a href="https://www.itzikbs.com/category/research-blog" rel="noopener" target="_blank">blog</a>. Feel free to <a href="https://www.itzikbs.com/contact/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">contact me</a> with any questions!
        </p>
